{meta: title Two Lonely People}
{meta: artist Moe Bandy}
{meta: composer Ed Penney and Tom Benjamin}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]It was dark it was lonely it was late it was [F]Monday
[G7]And I was looking and she was sitting at the [C]bar
[F]She was crying and I was trying to get her attention
[G7]But she didn't seem to notice that I was standing there at [C]all
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]Two lonely [G7]people  one lonely [C]night
[G7]Nothing behind us nothing in [C]sight
[F]The later [G7]it got  the more it looked [C]right
[F]For two lonely [C]people  one [G7]lonely [C]night
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]She looked up and I was smiling  I filled her glass
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
And she stopped crying
[G7]It was late it was Monday it was [C]free
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
And they were playing some old love song
[F]Though I hadn't danced in so long
[G7]She took me by the hand and I held her close to [C]me
{end_of_verse}

